Mexican international Hirving Lozano on Thursday completed his move to Serie A runners-up Napoli on a deal reported to be worth 42 million euros ($46 million). <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1244296" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lozano.jpg?resize=640%2C456&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="456" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lozano.jpg?w=680&amp;ssl=1 680w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lozano.jpg?resize=300%2C214&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lozano.jpg?resize=58%2C41&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lozano.jpg?resize=260%2C185&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lozano.jpg?resize=182%2C130&amp;ssl=1 182w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lozano.jpg?resize=560%2C399&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The 24-year-old winger arrives from PSV Eindhoven where he won the Dutch title in 2018. “Welcome Hirving,” Napoli club owner Aurelio De Laurentiis wrote on Twitter without revealing details of the transfer. Lozano, nicknamed ‘Chucky’, joined PSV from Pachuca in 2017 for 12.5 million euros and scored 45 goals in 83 games over two seasons. READ ALSO: `Gimme a name for my Album,’ Davido appeals to fans “I leave PSV as a happy man,” Lozano told the Dutch club’s website. “Winning the Dutch title was one of the highlights in my career so far and I also achieved my dream of playing UEFA Champions League.” Lozano has reportedly agreed a five-year deal worth 42 million euros which will earn him up to 4.5 million euros a year. The contract includes a 130 million euro buy-out clause, Sky Sports Italia reported. Lozano will not play in Napoli’s Serie A opener Saturday at Fiorentina, but is expected to make his debut against champions Juventus in Turin on August 31. VANGUARD Cristiano Ronaldo's move to Juventus has injected an air of expectation into the Italian championship not felt in decades while spending has smashed the one billion euro mark with more than a day still to go before the transfer window closes. August 16, 2018 In "Sports" Barcelona and Brazil defender Marlon completed a move to Serie A side Sassuolo Thursday on the eve of the closure of the transfer window in Italy. August 17, 2018 In "Sports" As the sole survivor of a coaching shuffle among the leading challengers, Carlo Ancelotti could have the best chance to end Napoli's 30-year wait for the Serie A title. August 21, 2019 In "News"